itl.enabler.api.types

Enum DeliveryTypes

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DeliveryTypes>
      • itl.enabler.api.types.DeliveryTypes
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DeliveryTypes>

    public enum DeliveryTypes
extends java.lang.Enum<DeliveryTypes>
    The type of delivery associated with a transaction.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      ATTENDANT
      A cleared transaction that was authorised for an attendant.
      AVAILABLE_PREAUTH
      A legacy unsold preauth transaction, also known as the current transaction.
      AVAILABLE_PREPAY_REFUND
      A legacy unsold prepay transaction, also known as the current transaction.
      CURRENT
      An unsold transaction, also known as the current transaction.
      DRIVE_OFF
      A transaction cleared by calling the Transaction.clear(TransactionClearTypes) method with a TransactionClearTypes argument of DRIVE_OFF.
      MONITOR
      A transaction cleared automatically by the Pump Server.
      NORMAL
      A transaction cleared by calling the Transaction.clear(TransactionClearTypes) method with a TransactionClearTypes argument of NORMAL.
      OFFLINE
      This type indicates an unexpected change in electronic totals.
      Possible reasons : Pump was switched to stand-alone(disconnected) mode and then deliveries were made.
      PREAUTH
      A transaction cleared by calling the legacy Delivery.ClearPreauth.
      PREPAY
      A transaction started by calling the legacy Pump.AuthorisePrepay.
      PREPAY_REFUND
      A legacy prepay refund transaction that has been cleared (refunded to the customer).
      PREPAY_REFUND_LOST
      A legacy prepay refund transaction that was cleared automatically by the Pump Server after the configured timeout period.
      REINSTATED
      A previously cleared transaction that has been reinstated for re-finalisation by calling the Transaction.reinstate method after being looked up with the Forecourt.getTransactionById or Forecourt.getTransactionByReference methods.
      STACKED
      An unsold transaction pushed onto the transaction stack.
      TEST
      A transaction cleared by calling the Transaction.clear(TransactionClearTypes) method with a TransactionClearTypes argument of TEST.
      UNKNOWN
      Transaction type is curently unknown.

      • OFFLINE

        public static final DeliveryTypes OFFLINE
        This type indicates an unexpected change in electronic totals.
        Possible reasons :
        • Pump was switched to stand-alone(disconnected) mode and then deliveries were made. When the pump is reconnected an offline delivery for the total of stand-alone deliveries will be logged by the Enabler.
        • Pump rounds totals to the nearest integer instead of matching the display format.
        • Internal error in the pump or Enabler system.

        If the pump has not been disconnected from Enabler, this type should not occur. If it happens regularly contact ITL support for help.

      • PREAUTH

      • PREPAY_REFUND

        public static final DeliveryTypes PREPAY_REFUND

      • PREPAY_REFUND_LOST

        public static final DeliveryTypes PREPAY_REFUND_LOST
        A legacy prepay refund transaction that was cleared automatically by the Pump Server after the configured timeout period. This is called a lost refund because the customer did not receive a refund.

      • REINSTATED

        public static final DeliveryTypes REINSTATED
        A previously cleared transaction that has been reinstated for re-finalisation by calling the Transaction.reinstate method after being looked up with the Forecourt.getTransactionById or Forecourt.getTransactionByReference methods.

      • STACKED
